s and scholars alike.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEnglish fiction. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Canadian.2bisacsh1 aAckerley, Chris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDoyen, Vik, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcCarthy, Patrick A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcCarthy, Patrick A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMota, Miguel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTiessen, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2014z978311127407208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2014z978311127709740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780776621807?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780776621807423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780776621807/original  a978-3-11-127407-2  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2014b2014  a978-3-11-127709-7  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2014b2014  aGBV-deGruyter-alles